LAGOS  – Daily Independent journalist, Sylvester Enoghase, has been recognised for his outstanding and courageous reporting at the ‘2021 MAN Re­porter Of The Year Award’ for Investigative Reporting. He emerged second position in the Newspaper Category, scoring 83 points, while the New Telegraph, journalist, Mr Taiwo Hassan, who scored 86 points came first. Winner of the Television Category; Mrs Nkeiru Nwoke­di, of AIT scored 74 points, while second place winner; Mr Abiola Ismail, MITV scored 65 points. Guinness MD Calls For Removal Of Women’s Inhibition At Work… Enugu Bans Keke, Okada, Tipper-Truck Operations Two LGAs Winner of the Radio Cate­gory, Mrs Ebere Obike, Radio Nigeria scored 79 points, while the second place winner Radio Category; Mrs Rhoda Ogun­seye, of Raypower scored 50 points Winner of the Online Cate­gory- Mrs Yemisi Izuora, Ori­ental News, scoring 65 points, while second place winner Online Category, Mr Simon Ugwu, Energy Frontier, scor­ing 63 points Winner of the Photojour­nalist Category, Mr Godwin Irekehe, New Telegraph, scor­ing 76 points, while the Second place winner Photo Journalist Category, Mr Olawale Amoo, Business Day, scoring 71 points.